<TITLE> Former BNP state minister bail rejected </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chandpur, March 18 (bdnews24.com)  A Chandpur Court on Thursday rejected the bail petition of former BNP state minister A. N. M. Ahsanul Milon who has been accused of attacking the car of an incumbent Awami League MP, Mohiuddin Khan Alamgir, seven years ago. On Sunday, Milon had surrendered to the district judge's court, after it ordered his arrest on January 18. The case, originally filed on 26 May 2009, alleges that on October 16 2003, Milon and his associates had attacked Mohiuddin's car while he was on his way from Dhaka to an Awami League meeting in Chandpur. In total, 34 people were accused, including Milon's wife. In the last parliamentary election in 2008, BNP candidate Milon lost to Alamgir. After the hearing, Milon's advocates Iqbal Bin Basar and Kamrul Islam told journalists that Milon has now been showed arrested in four other cases. Three related to attacking the Awami League office in Kashua and one case relating to financial irregularities in the election. bdne
